headline: Old Dominion notes softness in economy as one-month shipping volume declines
summary: In a sign that could be taken as lending credence to forecasts of an economic slowdown, Triad-based Old Dominion Freight Line, one of the country’s major trucking companies, said primary type of shipments decreased 14.4% in tons per day in May from a year earlier.  The decline in less-than-truckload tons per day came from a decrease in shipments per day of 11.4% and a decline on weight per shipment of 3.4%, Old Dominion said in an update of its May metrics Monday evening.  Quater to date, the company’s revenue per hundredweight excluding fuel surcharges increased nearly 8%, which Old Dominion attributed to its long-term pricing and service strategy aimed at building market share.
